com.epoch.assgts

Class Assgt

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.epoch.assgts.Assgt
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AssgtConstants, AppConstants, UserConstants

    public class Assgt
extends Object
implements AssgtConstants, UserConstants
    Holds the attributes of an assignment, including question, grading parameters, and extensions.

      • qGrps

        private transient List<AssgtQGroup> qGrps
        A list of AssgtQGroups, each of which contains a list of one or more questions. The questions are divided into an integral number of equal-sized bundles. Each AsstQGroup contains the number of questions in each question bundle and the number of bundles to pick when an assignment is instantiated, plus the points value of each question in the bundle.

      • gradingParams

        private String[][][] gradingParams
        Parameters used to adjust grades, as originally entered. First dimension represents attempt- or time-dependent grading; second dimension represents limits or factors; third dimension represents the serial number of the limits or factors. We use Oracle to do the calculations based on these values.

      • extensions

        private Map<String,String> extensions
        Map of students who have extensions, and the length of their extensions in days (usually) or minutes.
